# Cache Busting – Version Bumping Rule

Every time you edit a CSS or JS file, you MUST bump the version string in ALL of these files before committing.

## Version format

`YYYYMMDD-N` where N starts at 1 and increments if multiple deploys happen on the same day.
Today's date determines the prefix. Example: `20260227-1`, `20260227-2`, …

## Files to update (always ALL at once)

| File | What to change |
|------|----------------|
| `sw.js` | `const NEW_VERSION = '...'` + all `?v=` strings in STATIC_ASSETS |
| `index.html` | all `?v=` on `<link>` and `<script>` tags |
| `admin/index.html` | all `?v=` on `<script>` tags |
| `partner-entry/index.html` | all `?v=` on `<script>` tags |
| `taxi/index.html` | all `?v=` on `<script>` tags |
| `restavracije/index.html` | all `?v=` on `<link>` and `<script>` tags |
| `aktivnosti/index.html` | all `?v=` on `<link>` and `<script>` tags |
| `izgubljeno-nadjeno/index.html` | all `?v=` on `<script>` tags |

## Example

Old: `<link rel="stylesheet" href="./assets/app.css?v=20260227-1">`
New: `<link rel="stylesheet" href="./assets/app.css?v=20260228-1">`

Old in sw.js: `const NEW_VERSION = '20260227-1';`
New in sw.js: `const NEW_VERSION = '20260228-1';`

## Why this matters

The service worker caches files by exact URL (including `?v=`). Without bumping the version:
- Users see old CSS/JS even after Vercel deploys the new version
- PWA keš (cache) nikad ne osvježi automatski bez promjene URL-a
